TITLE: Storing Table State in Query String - PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to use Livewire attributes to store the table's filters, sorting, search, and pagination state in the URL query string. This allows users to access the same table state across requests. It requires the `Livewire\Attributes\Url` attribute.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/tables/docs/10-advanced.md#_snippet_19

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Livewire\Attributes\Url;

#[Url]
public bool $isTableReordering = false;

/**
 * @var array<string, mixed> | null
 */
#[Url]
public ?array $tableFilters = null;

#[Url]
public ?string $tableGrouping = null;

#[Url]
public ?string $tableGroupingDirection = null;

/**
 * @var ?string
 */
#[Url]
public $tableSearch = '';

#[Url]
public ?string $tableSortColumn = null;

#[Url]
public ?string $tableSortDirection = null;
```

