TITLE: Applying Global Tenant Scopes with Middleware in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates how to create a middleware to apply global scopes to Eloquent models, automatically scoping queries to the current tenant. This middleware is then registered for tenant-aware routes and made persistent to apply to all requests.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/panels/docs/11-tenancy.md#_snippet_35

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
<?php

namespace App\Http\Middleware;

use App\Models\Author;
use Closure;
use Filament\Facades\Filament;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Builder;
use Illuminate\Http\Request;

class ApplyTenantScopes
{
    public function handle(Request $request, Closure $next)
    {
        Author::addGlobalScope(
            fn (Builder $query) => $query->whereBelongsTo(Filament::getTenant()),
        );

        return $next($request);
    }
}

```

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Filament\Panel;

public function panel(Panel $panel): Panel
{
    return $panel
        // ...
        ->tenantMiddleware([
            ApplyTenantScopes::class,
        ], isPersistent: true);
}

```

