TITLE: Multiple Active Indicators for Filament Filters
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates rendering multiple active indicators by returning an array of `Indicator` objects. It formats 'from' and 'until' dates and uses `removeField()` to ensure the correct field is reset when removing the filter.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/tables/docs/04-filters/05-custom.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Carbon\Carbon;
use Filament\Forms\Components\DatePicker;
use Filament\Tables\Filters\Filter;
use Filament\Tables\Filters\Indicator;

Filter::make('created_at')
    ->form([
        DatePicker::make('from'),
        DatePicker::make('until'),
    ])
    // ...
    ->indicateUsing(function (array $data): array {
        $indicators = [];

        if ($data['from'] ?? null) {
            $indicators[] = Indicator::make('Created from ' . Carbon::parse($data['from'])->toFormattedDateString())
                ->removeField('from');
        }

        if ($data['until'] ?? null) {
            $indicators[] = Indicator::make('Created until ' . Carbon::parse($data['until'])->toFormattedDateString())
                ->removeField('until');
        }

        return $indicators;
    })
```

