TITLE: Using a Wizard as a Modal Form (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to use a Filament PHP wizard as a modal form using the `steps()` method. The wizard consists of multiple steps defined using `Step` objects, each containing a schema of form components. The example includes steps for 'Name', 'Description', and 'Visibility'.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/actions/docs/04-modals.md#_snippet_3

