TITLE: Accessing Action Arguments in the Action Method (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This PHP code shows how to access arguments passed to an action within the action's `action` closure. It retrieves the post ID from the `$arguments` array and uses it to find and delete the corresponding Post model. Requires the `App\Models\Post` model.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/actions/docs/06-adding-an-action-to-a-livewire-component.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use App\Models\Post;
use Filament\Actions\Action;

public function deleteAction(): Action
{
    return Action::make('delete')
        ->requiresConfirmation()
        ->action(function (array $arguments) {
            $post = Post::find($arguments['post']);

            $post?->delete();
        });
}
```

