TITLE: Custom Column Span in Grid (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to customize the number of grid columns consumed by each component at different breakpoints (lg and 2xl). It sets the 'name' and 'job' stack to occupy the full width on large screens and 2 columns on extra-large screens. The 'phone' column also occupies 2 columns on extra-large screens. Requires Filament Tables package.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/tables/docs/06-layout.md#_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Filament\Tables\Columns\Layout\Grid;
use Filament\Tables\Columns\Layout\Stack;
use Filament\Tables\Columns\TextColumn;

Grid::make([
    'lg' => 2,
    '2xl' => 5,
])
    ->schema([
        Stack::make([
            TextColumn::make('name'),
            TextColumn::make('job'),
        ])->columnSpan([
            'lg' => 'full',
            '2xl' => 2,
        ]),
        TextColumn::make('phone')
            ->icon('heroicon-m-phone')
            ->columnSpan([
                '2xl' => 2,
            ]),
        TextColumn::make('email')
            ->icon('heroicon-m-envelope'),
    ])
```

