TITLE: Asserting Modal Content using Pest
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to assert the content of a modal in a Filament action using Pest. It creates an invoice, retrieves the recipient's email, mounts the `EditInvoice` Livewire component, mounts the 'send' action, and asserts that the modal contains the recipient's email address using `assertSee()`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/actions/docs/09-testing.md#_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use function Pest\Livewire\livewire;

it('confirms the target address before sending', function () {
    $invoice = Invoice::factory()->create();
    $recipientEmail = $invoice->company->primaryContact->email;

    livewire(EditInvoice::class, [
        'invoice' => $invoice,
    ])
        ->mountAction('send')
        ->assertSee($recipientEmail);
});
```

