TITLE: Populate Chart Data with Treatments per Month
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to fetch and format data for the chart. It uses the `laravel-trend` package to retrieve the number of treatments per month for the past year and formats the data into a structure suitable for the Chart.js library used by Filament.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/panels/docs/02-getting-started.md#_snippet_33

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use App\Models\Treatment;
use Flowframe\Trend\Trend;
use Flowframe\Trend\TrendValue;

protected function getData(): array
{
    $data = Trend::model(Treatment::class)
        ->between(
            start: now()->subYear(),
            end: now(),
        )
        ->perMonth()
        ->count();

    return [
        'datasets' => [
            [
                'label' => 'Treatments',
                'data' => $data->map(fn (TrendValue $value) => $value->aggregate),
            ],
        ],
        'labels' => $data->map(fn (TrendValue $value) => $value->date),
    ];
}
```

