TITLE: Dispatching Livewire Events from Notification Actions - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates dispatching a Livewire event when a notification action is clicked using JavaScript with Filament. The `dispatch()` method sends the event. `dispatchSelf` and `dispatchTo` are also shown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/filamentphp/filament/blob/3.x/packages/notifications/docs/02-sending-notifications.md#_snippet_20

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
new FilamentNotification()
    .title('Saved successfully')
    .success()
    .body('Changes to the post have been saved.')
    .actions([
        new FilamentNotificationAction('view')
            .button()
            .url('/view')
            .openUrlInNewTab(),
        new FilamentNotificationAction('undo')
            .color('gray')
            .dispatch('undoEditingPost'),
    ])
    .send()
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
new FilamentNotificationAction('undo')
    .color('gray')
    .dispatchSelf('undoEditingPost')

new FilamentNotificationAction('undo')
    .color('gray')
    .dispatchTo('another_component', 'undoEditingPost')
```

